  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON:  The mansard roof extensions would break the otherwise unbroken roofline of his terrace row resulting in a harmful interruption, the design of the extensions, by reason of the unsatisfactory proportions, the appearance of the windows and the introduction of rear roof terraces and railings, are obtrusive and uncharacteristic additions. The extensions would have a significantly detrimental impact on the character and appearance of the Conservation Area and the host buildings of the terrace which they form part, contrary to policies  D4, D11, D22 and D25 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan (2002), policies CS8 and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011, policies 7.4 and 7.8 of the London Plan 2011 and the Canonbury Conservation Area Design Guidelines, Supplementary Planning Guidance ‘Planning Standards’ and the Islington Urban Design Guide."
